   <note>This letter from Andrew Jackson to Rachel Jackson was written from Jones Bend, Cumberland (Knoxville), on May 9, 1796. It is a love letter, filled with expressions of affection and hope for the future. Jackson spoke of retiring from public life, longing to spend his days in "domestick sweetness," citing such a life as his "only ambition and ultimate wish."</note>
